Quote:  I was an Officer Cadet - a grand sounding title, but a cadet is generally acknowledged to be one rank lower than the Regimental cat. Worse yet, I was a baggy on basic. <i>Ibid.</i> 18 As new recruits beginning basic training (baggy-arse trousers gave us our nickname), we comprehended almost none of the myriad abbreviations, acronyms or slang.
